nt to this rant, I just wanted to vent a bit about one of the irratating things we all have to put up with in eq.<br><br>Traab &quot;Love Machine&quot; Fellhammer<br>Human Mob Compactor of the 51st Cycle<br>And Almost Too Sexy To Live!<br><br>&quot;Thank god I normally have sow heading into cc so I can easily outrun the orcs to town without taking any real damage.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/02 2:27:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=904.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pointless mob aggro</span><hr size=1> I agree, green mobs should : <br><br>A) leave me be in fear of my wrath  <br><br>B) run away and hide from me on sight ( not going to get <br>friends because they would die too )<br><br>Or my favorite,<br><br>C) be killed with one push of a button that uses the same timer as disarm ( with no loot/group exp ) <br><br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a><BR> 55th Human Myrmidon of the Eternal Bloodguard <BR>Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/30/02 10:56:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=904.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pointless mob aggro</span><hr size=1> I am kinda fond of choice c personally lol. I can understand WHY these oh so very green mobs attack me when I wander around their home, I mean after all, why would my enimies just let me walk past a group of them without trying to stop me? Its just ANNOYING! Not to mention the potential embarrasment of being killed off by a swarm of them.<br>A 50 warrior in my guild was once exploring the tunnels in the up top area of cc when he got swarmed badly. He managed to survive the first wave and get to a safe spot but then was trapped a long way from any zoneline with about a million angry mobs out for his blood. I had to go in and rescue him with my 45 druid so we could port out of there. (superior camo is your friend!) As a monk the only time I could ever be &quot;trapped&quot; by greens is if I was surrounded by casters since I can feign flop my way through any zone just about so I cant even imagine how embarrassing and frustrating it would be to be imprisoned by mobs that you can kill off a dozen at a time simply because there are now TWO dozen around you lol.<br><br>Traab &quot;Love Machine&quot; Fellhammer<br>Human Mob Compactor of the 51st Cycle<br>And Almost Too Sexy To Live!<br><br>&quot;/gu can someone help me? Im stuck in sola surrounded by level 20 wizards. /gag&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucslochraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/30/02 5:44:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=904.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=